🧠 2) DSA — SLIDING WINDOW (BASIC)
🔹 Concept
Maintain a window of size k over array/list
Efficiently compute sums, maximum, or frequency counts
Example: Maximum Sum of Subarray Size k
def max_sum(arr, k):
    window_sum = sum(arr[:k])
    max_sum = window_sum
    for i in range(k, len(arr)):
        window_sum += arr[i] - arr[i-k]
        max_sum = max(max_sum, window_sum)
    return max_sum
Time: O(n)
Space: O(1)
Example: Sliding Window Frequency
from collections import defaultdict

def count_freq_window(arr, k):
    freq = defaultdict(int)
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        freq[arr[i]] += 1
        if i >= k:
            freq[arr[i-k]] -= 1
    return freq
